<h2>Find large files on a Linux / Mac OS X machine</h2>
<p>The following should owrk on your Mac OS X</p>
<pre>
  sudo find / -type f -size +20000k -exec ls -lh {} \; | awk '{ print $9 ": " $5 }'
</pre>

<p>For a linux (tested on Ubuntu), the $9 most liley needs to be an $8</p>

<pre>
  sudo find / -type f -size +20000k -exec ls -lh {} \; | awk '{ print <strong>$8</strong> ": " $5 }'
</pre>

</div>
